About Us
Good Life Station is part of Optimal’s Smart City Program and will provide a destination for people to connect with the community while engaging and enlightening residents and visitors about the city's unique history and heritage, local news, businesses, events, and education opportunities.
We’d love to connect with you!
Whether you’re curious about our Stations or excited to plan something special in our event space or media rooms, our team is ready to support you.

Entrepreneur Thrive Series
Quang Tran is an entrepreneur and mentor dedicated to helping startups build strong teams, great products, and lasting companies. As co-founder of LaunchPad at Infinity Hall and Starter Space, he has played a key role in shaping Gainesville’s entrepreneurial ecosystem and serves on the board of the Gainesville Tech Council.
How to Scale Your Business with AI & Agentic Workflows with Quang Tran
Leverage AI. Streamline Workflows. Scale Smarter.
September 15th, 2025
6:00 pm - 7:30 pm
Good Life Station
Register
Teddy is an award-winning innovator and CTO of Optimal Station, leading advancements in automation, robotics, and smart city solutions. Recognized as one of Automatic Merchandiser’s “Pros to Know,” he pioneers technologies that enhance connectivity, sustainability, and user experience, while mentoring the next generation of leaders.
Small Business to Thrive by Using AI with Teddy Sanchez
Unlock Growth, Efficiency, and Opportunity with AI.
January 30th, 2025
6:00 pm - 7:30 pm
Good Life Station
Register
Shelly is a strategic growth leader and community connector, building brands and relationships where marketing meets purpose and opportunity. With experience in the construction and nonprofit sectors, she brings expertise in marketing, operations, and event management, backed by a BBA in Marketing from Saint Leo University.
The Shelly Approach: Marketing, Networking, & Branding Simplified with Shelly Vickers
Simplify Your Strategy. Amplify Your Impact.
May 19th, 2025
6:00 pm - 7:30 pm
Good Life Station
Register
James is a seasoned entrepreneur, community leader, and CEO of Phalanx Defense Systems. As Executive Director of Community Engagement & Continuing Education at Santa Fe College, he combines business expertise, creativity, and community passion to drive economic growth and inspire the next generation of leaders in North Florida.
The Art of the Ask with James Coats
Elevate Your Voice. Amplify Your Results.
November 17th, 2025
6:00 pm - 7:30 pm
Good Life Station
Register
Laurence has over 20 years of experience in strategy and consulting, supporting entrepreneurs and small businesses in the U.S. and the Caribbean. He currently serves as Program Coordinator for the Bradford County Incubator, helping local innovators grow their ideas into thriving ventures.
Entrepreneurial Mindset Hacks with Laurence Andrews
Master the Mindset That Fuels Innovation and Growth.
March 17th, 2025
6:00 pm - 7:30 pm
Good Life Station
Register
Boaz is an experienced entrepreneur and problem-solver with over 25 years of expertise. With a strong background in marketing, he has helped businesses and organizations grow by crafting creative strategies, building strong networks, and finding solutions that drive results. Boaz’s entrepreneurial spirit and ability to think outside the box make him a valuable resource for both business and community growth.
Entrepreneurial Thinking with Boaz Santiago
Cultivating the Mindset of Tomorrow’s Leaders.
July 21st, 2025
6:00 pm - 7:30 pm
